9:T42e,<p>Stacking happens when a business owner takes a second, third, or even fourth MCA while still repaying the first. Each new advance adds another daily payment pulled from your bank account.</p>

<h2 id="what-stacking">What is stacking?</h2>
<p>Multiple advances mean multiple daily debits. Your cash flow gets squeezed from every direction. Many providers know about stacking and some actively encourage it — a second provider might offer more cash knowing you're already stretched thin.</p>

<h2 id="costs">The real combined cost</h2>
<p>The combined cost can be devastating. We've seen businesses paying the equivalent of 200–350% APR across stacked advances. Each provider files a UCC lien against your business; if things go wrong, they'll fight each other — and you — over who gets paid first.</p>

<h2 id="avoid">How to avoid the trap</h2>
<p>Before taking another advance, run the numbers. Use our free tool to analyze your current contract and see your true APR. Then model what adding another advance would do to your daily payments and total cost.</p>2:[["$","article",null,{"className":"mx-auto max-w-[1008px] px-4 py-12 sm:px-6 lg:flex lg:gap-12","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"min-w-0 flex-1 lg:max-w-[var(--max-width-text)]","children":[["$","nav",null,{"className":"text-[var(--text-sm)]","style":{"color":"var(--color-text-secondary)"},"aria-label":"Breadcrumb","children":[["$","$L7",null,{"href":"/","className":"transition hover:underline","children":"Home"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"mx-2","children":"/"}],["$","$L7",null,{"href":"/blog","className":"transition hover:underline","children":"Blog"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"mx-2","children":"/"}],["$","span",null,{"style":{"color":"var(--color-text-primary)"},"children":"MCA Basics"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"mx-2","children":"/"}],["$","span",null,{"style":{"color":"var(--color-text-tertiary)"},"children":"Why Stacking Multiple MCAs Is So Dangerous"}]]}],["$","span",null,{"className":"mt-4 inline-block badge badge-safe","style":{"background":"#00D4A820","borderColor":"#00D4A850","color":"#00D4A8"},"children":"MCA Basics"}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"mt-4 font-display text-3xl leading-tight md:text-[3rem]","style":{"color":"var(--color-text-primary)"},"children":"Why Stacking Multiple MCAs Is So Dangerous"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"mt-6 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex h-8 w-8 items-center justify-center rounded-full font-mono text-sm font-medium","style":{"background":"var(--color-accent-muted)","color":"var(--color-accent-primary)"},"children":"F"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-[var(--text-base)] font-medium","style":{"color":"var(--color-text-primary)"},"children":"FundingWatch Research Team"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"font-mono text-[var(--text-sm)]",